 "text": "\nAfter 24+ days of uptime, system collects SYN_RCVD entries\n\nI have been seeing a problem identical to that reported in:\n\nhttp://lists.freebsd.org/pipermail/freebsd-current/2007-November/080327.html\n\nI'm running a DELL PowerEdge 1550 system built from 7.0-CURRENT\nsources sup'ed on Aug 4th with a GENERIC config (dmesg.boot at bottom\nof message).\n\n% cat /sys/i386/conf/PE1550 \ninclude GENERIC\n\nin /etc/rc.conf:\n# phil 8/23/2007\n# set net.inet.tcp.always_keepalive=0\ntcp_keepalive=\"NO\"\n\n% uptime\n11:25AM  up 55 days,  7:14, 5 users, load averages: 0.00, 0.05, 0.06\n% netstat -n -p tcp | grep SYN_RCVD | wc\n    4473   26838  339948\n% sysctl net.inet.tcp.syncache\nnet.inet.tcp.syncache.rst_on_sock_fail: 1\nnet.inet.tcp.syncache.rexmtlimit: 3\nnet.inet.tcp.syncache.hashsize: 512\nnet.inet.tcp.syncache.count: 4473\nnet.inet.tcp.syncache.cachelimit: 15360\nnet.inet.tcp.syncache.bucketlimit: 30\n\n% netstat -s | sed -n '/sync/,/rec/p' \n\t1187046 syncache entries added\n\t\t28961 retransmitted\n\t\t17175 dupsyn\n\t\t0 dropped\n\t\t1169985 completed\n\t\t696 bucket overflow\n\t\t0 cache overflow\n\t\t6618 reset\n\t\t5098 stale\n\t\t97 aborted\n\t\t0 badack\n\t\t50 unreach\n\t\t0 zone failures\n\t1187046 cookies sent\n\t275 cookies received\n\nI had seen this problem once before and have been running this script\nhourly:\n\n% more tcp-states.sh\necho ''\ndate\nuptime\nnetstat -p tcp | awk '/^tcp/ { print $6 }' | sort | uniq -c\n\nThe latest entry:\n% tail -7 tcp-states.log\n11:35AM  up 55 days,  7:24, 5 users, load averages: 0.00, 0.00, 0.00\n   8 ESTABLISHED\n   1 FIN_WAIT_1\n   4 FIN_WAIT_2\n  14 LAST_ACK\n4473 SYN_RCVD\n   8 TIME_WAIT\n\n% cat post.awk\n/2007/ {\n    if (up \u0026\u0026 syn_rcvd) print up, \"=\u003e\", syn_rcvd\n    up = syn_rcvd = \"\"\n}\n\n/up/ {\n    sub(\"^.*up\", \"\");\n    sub(\", [0-9]+ user.*\", \"\");\n    up = $0\n}\n\n/SYN_RCVD/ { syn_rcvd = $1 }\n\n(note the buildup begins after 24 days, 20 hours of uptime -- 2^31 